Introduce a slight delay in changing the min height of an output area that is cleared to prevent jitter.

When an output area is cleared and then quickly replaced with other output, the quickly changing height causes the page to jitter. This happens a lot with ipywidget @interact, for example. This 50ms delay seems small enough to take care of the problem, but could be tweaked.

An example that shows this jitter is this:

```python
from ipywidgets import interact, Output, HBox
left = Output()
right = Output()
with left:
    @interact(x=(0,10))
    def f(x):
        @interact(y=(0,x))
        def g(y):
            with right:
                print('Product',x*y)

print("Product calculator")
HBox([left, right])
```

Improve scroll behavior for active cells.

In this commit, we decouple setting a cell as active and scrolling to show it. This is useful when, for example, you are making a cell active by clicking on it. Clicking indicates a point of interest in the cell (like a position in the input editor, or a particular output slider you want to interact with), and scrolling when these click events make a cell active disrupts the users focus on the part they want to interact with. On the other hand, programmatically setting the active cell often does involve scrolling, so we added a method to explicitly scroll to the active cell.

renderers/index.css: Adjust HTML table style

Port changes made to Jupyter notebook tables in Issue 2209 and Pull
Request 2231. Set the max-width to none so that libraries like Pandas
which want to set the max width can do it properly.

default-theme: Show close icon even if dirty

When the tab is dirty (unsaved changes), it used to show a dot. This is
confusing for new users, so the new approach is to show a black dot with
a white cross in it.
Clean up path an url functions

notebook: Remove celltoolbar if not notebook

If the current Panel is not a NotebookPanel, remove the cell toolbar tab
from the left menu. Show it only when the Panel is a NotebookPanel.

renderers: No margin for second level lists

There was a margin put in lists to separate it from paragraphs,
header, and other tags in general. But this margin is also causing a
space in the second level list if the first level list item has a html
tag. Hence, we add a new CSS selector which sets the margin in this case
back to 0.

rendermime: Don't stop if error in canRender

In rendermime, if an error occured when the canRender() function is
called, the notebook should not stop and break. Rather it should
continue and attempt others.

images: Remove search.svg in favor of icons

THe icons folder has the search.svg and that is the one being used in
the CSS. The search.svg in images is a copy of this and is not being
used anywhere. To avoid confusion and duplication - remove it

running/index.css: Use refresh.svg from icon

The refresh.svg that running/index.css was using was from images and not
icons. This led to the same svg file being duplicated. Remove the
images/refresh.svg and use the icons/md/refresh.svg instead.

images: Remove .jp-FolderIcon already in icon

The icon.css already has a .jp-FolderIcon which sets the background url
to landingfolder.svg. For some reason the class and svg file are
duplicated in images.css and default-theme/images. This is unnecessary
duplication - so, remove it from images and use icons instead.

landing/index.css: Align Landing-folder and path

The Landing folder was not in vertical alignment with the Landing-path.
This fixes the vertical alignment by setting the :before which handles
the baseline problem and also sets the line-height to 1em to ensure the
alignment is correct.

launcher/index.css: Align Landing folder and path

The LandingWidget-folder was not in vertical alignment with the
LandingWidget-path. This fixes the vertical alignment by setting
the :before which handles the baseline problem and also sets the
line-height to 1em to ensure the alignment is correct.

tabs.css: Unify Landscape and portrait TabIcon

The TabIcon had 2 different styles for Landscape and Portrait. Unify
them into a single one. The earlier style was not vertical aligned
correctly and the current unified style handles this properly.

handle surrogate pair offsets in cursor_pos

Jupyter protocol defines cursor_pos as unicode character offset.
javascript stores high-codepoint offsets as utf16 "surrogate pairs",
counting as two code points in js string indices.

Adds coreutils.Text transforms back and forth between the two index calculations.
